                        <msContents>
                            <summary>
                                The author has been living in the Saljuq era and at the court of Sulṭān Sanjar, and has created this work upon his request in 17 chapters.
                                The first to fifth chapters are about foods as well as plain and compound drugs, and the sixth to seventeenth chapters about the issues around sexual intercourse.
                            </summary>
                        <msItem>
                            <locus from="53a" to="88b">ff. 53a-88b</locus>
                            <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                            <note type="content-genre">Medicine</note>
                            <title xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" key="work_11202">Tuḥfat al-mulūk fī laẕẕāt al-mubāshirāt</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ara" key="work_11202">تحفة الملوک فی لذات المباشرات</title>
                            <author key="person_f5965">
                                <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Haybat Allāh ibn Azdah Mushīr ibn Jānī ibn Jāmās, active 13th century</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="per">هیبت‌الله بن ازده مشیر بن جانی بن جاماس، قرن ۷ هجری</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" cert="low">Haybat Allāh Zayd Baṣrī</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="per" type="alt" cert="low">هیبت‌الله زید بصری</persName>
                            </author>
                            <incipit xml:lang="per">
                                بسمله، حمدله، اما بعد بدانکه مصنف این کتاب هیبت‌الله بن ازده مشیر بن جانی بن جاماس می‌گوید که چون به شرف خدمت… ابوالهارث سنجر بن ملکشاه 
                                رحمه الله مشرف شدم… بنده را بخلوتگاه خود و از اسرار خود چندین بر لفظ مبارک پادشاه فرمود که… درین باب اشارت رفت و کتابی ساخت از مجامعت… شرط بندگی بجای آورد
                                و در حقایق و دقایق این کتاب جهد تمام کرد…
                            </incipit>
                            <explicit xml:lang="per">
                                … بادام تلخ پنج درم دارچین سه درم زنجبیل سه درم عسل سه وزن ادویه… سه دوم.                            
                            </explicit>
                            <colophon xml:lang="per">
                                تمت الکتاب بعون الله الملک و الوهاب فی… شهر شوال… سنه ۱۱۹۲.
                            </colophon>
                            <listBibl>
                                <head>Sequence Number in the Persian Catalogue:</head>
                                <bibl><choice><abbr>FAW</abbr><expan>Ferdowsi Library, Wadham College, University of Oxford - Minasian Collection</expan></choice> 167</bibl>
                            </listBibl>
                            <listBibl>
                                <head>Similar Copies in Other Libraries:</head>
                                <bibl type="alternative-version"><choice><abbr>MAJ</abbr><expan>Library, Museum and Documentation Center of the Islamic Consultative Assembly</expan></choice> 2/297</bibl>
                            </listBibl>
                            <listBibl>
                                <head>Printed editions:</head>
                                <bibl type="printed-version">Tehran, 1388 Shamsī/2010</bibl>
                            </listBibl>
                            <note>
                                According to the existing catalogues, there are only two copies left of this work, one in the Majlis Library of Iran, and one in Neẓāmiyah of Ḥaydar'ābād.                                
                                The printed copy is also based on the manuscript held in Neẓāmiyah of Ḥaydar'ābād Dakan. Therefore, the current copy included, only three copies have survived from this work.
                                The current copy is also important in respect of the author's name, which is recorded as Haybat Allāh ibn Azdah Mushīr ibn Janī ibn Jāmās, while it is listed as Haybat Allāh Zayd Baṣrī in the other two copies.
                                As he has been working in the court of the Saljuqs, the second name does not seem to be reliably correct.
                            </note>
                        </msItem>
